CodeList.Name: Ophthalmic Focus of Study Specific Interest

Description.TranslatedText: Terminology relevant to the identification of a focus of ophthalmic observations.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The eye positioned in the right orbit, Oculus Dexter.
The eye positioned in the left orbit, Oculus Sinister.
Of or pertaining to both the left and right eyes, Oculus Uterque.

CodeList.nciodm:CDISCSynonym: Ophthalmic Focus of Study Specific Interest
CodeList.nciodm:PreferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Ophthalmic Focus of Study Specific Interest Terminology
